The pre-commit and pre-push gitleaks hooks live in .git/hooks/
which is not tracked or cloned. New clones don't get them. This is
actually correct for the underground principle — hooks are local
setup, not imposed on other users. But it means the gitleaks
protection requires per-clone setup.

Options for portability without violating underground:
- activate command could install hooks (opt-in)
- document in SKILL.md 'On arrival' section
- a future 'mycelium.sh setup' command

Do NOT put hooks in a tracked .githooks/ directory — that would
make mycelium visible in the working tree.
